Package com.phasmidsoftware.dsaipg.graphs.union_find

Interface TypedUF<T>

Type Parameters:
T - the type of elements over which the union-find operations are performed
All Superinterfaces:
Connections, UF
All Known Implementing Classes:
TypedUF_HWQUPC
public interface TypedUF<T> extends UF
TypedUF is an extension of the UF interface where elements are not limited to integers, but can be represented by objects of a generic type T. This interface allows union-find operations to be performed on generic types.

    • union

      void union(T t1, T t2) throws UFException
      Merges the components containing the two specified elements. This operation connects two elements such that they belong to the same set.
      Parameters:
      t1 - the first element to be merged
      t2 - the second element to be merged
      Throws:
      UFException - if an error occurs during the union operation, such as invalid or unrecognized elements
